# artifacts/ (deliverables)

`artifacts/` is for final deliverables that should be easy to find and share.

Rules:

- Put final deliverables here; keep intermediate work in `logs/`.
- If the user needs a temporary holding area for non-deliverable files, use `temp/` rather than `artifacts/`.
- Use per-task subfolders: `artifacts/<short-desc>/<run-folder>/`.
- `run-folder` naming (local time): `YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS-<epochMs>-<short-desc>`.
  - Example: `artifacts/subaru-brz-ads/20260301-212955-1709309395257-subaru-brz-ads/`.
- Keep the `run-folder` name identical to the matching `logs/<short-desc>/<run-folder>/` run folder.
- Each run folder must include a `README.md` listing delivered files and any notes.
- Keep `artifacts/AGENTS.md` tracked in git even if `artifacts/` is ignored.
